30 April 2015  A screenshot from YouTube uploader Eric Nathans time-lapse video of Cape Town without electricity during load-shedding. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom is continuing to implement stage 2 load-shedding on Friday.
The blackouts have been happening from Wednesday and will end on Friday night at 11 pm although they could continue into the weekend. READ: Eskom continues with Stage 2 load-shedding The power utility says the decision was taken due to the loss of generation and urgent maintenance being performed at certain power stations.